Class PerformanceTests

  • java.lang.Object
    • fi.explorator.PerformanceTests

  • public class PerformanceTests
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to do Performance tests for Floyd-Warshall, Dijkstra and A* pathfinding algorithms. At the moment tests are being done to static map, where there are about 33% blocked cells. Cell count is 2304 and number of paths being resolved is 100. It might be good idea in the future to make cell count to rise progressively as well as path count, to get better idea of the performance of the algorithms.
